sentences: Mats Olsson (3 November 1929 – 11 September 2013) was a Swedish musician.
He was the musical director for the Swedish national final of the Eurovision Song Contest on multiple occasions in the 1960s and 1970s.
He was the conductor for the Swedish ESC entries in 1967, 1968 and 1972; as well as musical director of the Eurovision Song Contest 1975.
